<% if (ctx.compliance.hipaa) { -%>
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:BEGIN compliance-hipaa -->
## HIPAA notes

This project handles Protected Health Information. Key rules:

- No PHI in logs, error messages, or analytics events.
- All persistence layers must be BAA-covered services.
- Access to production data requires audit-logged break-glass.
- Run `security-review` skill before any PR touching auth, storage, or transport.
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:END compliance-hipaa -->
<% } -%>
<% if (ctx.compliance.pci) { -%>
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:BEGIN compliance-pci -->
## PCI notes

This project touches cardholder data. Key rules:

- Never log PAN, CVV, or full track data — even in debug builds.
- Tokenize at the earliest boundary; downstream services see tokens only.
- Quarterly ASV scan and annual SAQ are required artifacts.
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:END compliance-pci -->
<% } -%>
<% if (ctx.compliance.gdpr) { -%>
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:BEGIN compliance-gdpr -->
## GDPR notes

- Lawful basis must be documented for every processing activity.
- DSAR (export, delete, rectify) endpoints must exist and be tested.
- Data minimization: collect only what the feature requires.
<!-- CLAUDE-BOOTSTRAP:END compliance-gdpr -->
<% } -%>
